<TITLE> US offers to reinforce RAB, police </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Feb 8 (bdnews24.com)  The US on Sunday offered to provide Bangladesh assistance in reinforcing the law-enforcement agencies including the Rapid Action Battalion and the police, the law minister said. A four-member delegation of US Justice Department, led by Carr Trevillian, in a meeting with the minister, also offered to work jointly in curbing militancy and terrorism. "The government will give a positive support respond to the proposal of reinforcing the law-enforcing agencies," Shafiq Ahmed said. "We have held discussions on ways as to how the two countries can work together in handling terrorism. The US has placed a number of proposals on the matter," he told reporters after the meeting. "We have exchanged views initially, more discussions will be held later," he said. The law minister replied in the negative as he was asked whether they had talked about any deal on terrorism and militancy. b
